```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace(" " => "_", "-" => "_")
end
```
This function first lowers the case of the column name using `lowercase()`, then strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip()`, and finally replaces spaces (`" "`) and hyphens (`"-"`) with underscores (`"_"`) using `replace()`. The pipe operator `|>` is used to chain these functions together, allowing for a more readable and concise syntax.
